{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17519490","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17519490"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:11:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:11:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13029"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13029"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.47,0.3,0.07,0.13,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5466"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98610"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5466"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81009"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"141"},{"type":"tags","id":"1165"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"5783"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9273"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12252"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14392"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29387"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33444"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42840"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43380"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44600"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98610","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/98610"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 70-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine health check. She reports a six-month history of intermittent lower back pain and has noticed a decrease in her height of 4 cm over the past year. She experienced menopause at age 52 and has never taken hormone replacement therapy. Her mother sustained a hip fracture at age 70. She has no other significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She does not smoke or consume alcohol.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her height is 158 cm and weight is 54 kg (BMI 21.6 kg/m\u00b2). Her pulse rate is 72/min, blood pressure 130/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. She has mild tenderness over the lower thoracic and upper lumbar spine. Neurological examination of the lower limbs is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lumbar spine X-ray","Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry scan","Magnetic resonance imaging of the lumbar spine","Serum calcium and vitamin D levels","Nuclear medicine bone scan"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with several concerning features for vertebral fracture: significant height loss (4 cm), back pain, and multiple risk factors for osteoporosis including age, postmenopausal status, and family history. Given these findings, \u003Cstrong\u003Elumbar spine X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial investigation to assess for vertebral fractures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDual-energy X-ray absorptiometry scan\u003C/strong\u003E is indeed important in osteoporosis assessment, but in this case where there is clinical suspicion of vertebral fracture, X-ray imaging should be performed first. If vertebral fractures are confirmed (defined as loss of vertebral height \u226520%), this would establish the diagnosis of osteoporosis regardless of bone mineral density measurements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMagnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the lumbar spine\u003C/strong\u003E would be indicated if there were concerning neurological symptoms or signs suggesting nerve root compression, which are not present in this case. MRI is unnecessarily complex and expensive as an initial investigation for suspected osteoporotic vertebral fracture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum calcium and vitamin D levels\u003C/strong\u003E are useful in the workup of osteoporosis but are not the most appropriate first-line investigation when vertebral fracture is suspected. These would typically be checked after confirming the presence of fracture or osteoporosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENuclear medicine bone scan\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated as an initial investigation for suspected osteoporotic vertebral fracture. It would be more appropriate if there were concerns about metastatic disease, if the site of fracture was unclear, or a diagnosis of Paget\u0027s disease of the bone was suspected (consider if chronically elevated alkaline phosphatase). \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter X-ray imaging, if vertebral fractures are confirmed, the patient would require comprehensive osteoporosis assessment including DXA scanning, biochemical testing, and evaluation for secondary causes of osteoporosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Plain radiographs are the initial investigation of choice when vertebral fracture is suspected due to height loss and back pain.","Risk factors for osteoporosis include age over 65, female sex, early menopause, family history, and low body mass index.","Height loss of more than 2 cm should prompt investigation for vertebral fracture."],"references":["Krugh M, Langaker MD. Dual-Energy X-Ray Absorptiometry. [Updated 2023 Jun 5]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519042/","Porter JL, Varacallo M. Osteoporosis. [Updated 2023 Aug 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK441901/","RACGP. \u201cOsteoporosis Management and Fracture Prevention in Post-Menopausal Women and Men \u003E 50 Years of Age \u2013 Summary of Recommendations.\u201d RACGP, 2024, www.racgp.org.au/clinical-resources/clinical-guidelines/key-racgp-guidelines/view-all-racgp-guidelines/osteoporosis/summary-of-recommendations. Accessed 15 Apr. 2025."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81009"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13029"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81009","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/81009"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-15T18:48:16+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-15T18:49:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5466"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98610"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","lin